# JoodKitchen Project Rules

## Architecture Overview
- API-first design with 100% frontend/backend separation
- Symfony 6+ backend with API Platform
- CoreUI 5.x admin interface
- MySQL database with proper entity relationships
- JWT authentication with role-based access control
- Redis caching for performance optimization
- Mercure for real-time communications

## Core Business Logic
- Daily Menu System with 3 cuisine types (Moroccan, Italian, International)
- Weekly Subscription System with 5 meals/week
- Multi-role user system (Admin, Kitchen Staff, Delivery, Customer)
- Payment integration with Moroccan CMI credit cards and cash on delivery
- Comprehensive order management with CommandeArticle flexibility

## Development Standards
- Follow Symfony best practices and conventions
- Maintain proper entity relationships and cascading
- Use VichUploaderBundle for all file uploads
- Implement proper API versioning and documentation
- Ensure proper error handling and logging
- Use DataDogAuditBundle for operation tracking

## Security Requirements
- Never expose sensitive data in API responses
- Always use proper JWT token validation
- Implement CORS policies correctly
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Follow proper permission checking at all levels

